# ShieldKe Frontend — environment variables
#
# Copy this file to .env for local overrides (rarely needed — the
# code already falls back to localhost:5000 automatically when this
# isn't set, so local development works without any .env file).
#
# For the LIVE Vercel deployment, do NOT rely on a committed .env file
# (Vite reads these at BUILD time, and most teams don't commit .env to
# git anyway). Instead set this in Vercel's dashboard:
#   Project → Settings → Environment Variables → Add:
#     Name:  VITE_API_URL
#     Value: https://<your-render-backend-name>.onrender.com/api
#
# IMPORTANT: the value MUST end in /api — every fetch call in the
# codebase appends paths like /auth/login, /consultations, etc.
# directly onto this value. Leaving off /api means every request
# will 404 in production.
#
# After adding/changing this in Vercel, you must trigger a new
# deployment (Vercel's "Redeploy" button, or push a new commit).
# Vite bakes VITE_* variables into the build at BUILD time, not at
# runtime — so an existing deployment will keep using whatever value
# (or fallback) was present the last time it was built.

VITE_API_URL=https://your-backend-name.onrender.com/api
